{"questionId":"35019299","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Kacheena stands at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>K</mtext></math>, the top of a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>218</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> vertical cliff. The base of the cliff is located at&nbsp;point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>. A ship is located at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>S</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1200</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> from Kacheena.</p>\n<p>This information is shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/89c3edbf035c9a48ef01daea716db678000eb045.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down your answer to part (b) in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mi>k</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>10</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>18</mn></math><br>Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></math><br>Accept their rounded answer to part (b). <br>Award <em><strong>A0A0</strong></em> for answers of the type:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35019299","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.1c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down your answer to part (b) in the form a×10k where 1≤a<10 and k∈ℤ.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.1—Using standard form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}